{"lemma":"اِثْنانِ","slug":"اِثْنانِ","root":"ٱثنن","root_slug":"ٱثنن","root_link":"/words/roots/ٱثنن","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["num"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n252","n4780"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A7%D9%90%D8%AB%D9%92%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"num","gloss":"two","examples":[{"text":"رَأَيْتُ رَجُلَيْنِ ٱثْنَيْنِ وَٱمْرَأَتَيْنِ ٱثْنَتَيْنِ","english":"I saw [only] two men and two women."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Etymology tree\nProto-Semitic *ṯin-\nArabic اثنان\nInherited from Proto-Semitic *ṯin-."},"ipa":["/iθ.naːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n252","headword_ar":"اِثْنَانِ","root":"Avn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AivonataAni","text_ar":"اِثْنَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vnY","text_ar":"ثنى"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n4780","headword_ar":"اِثْنَانِ","root":"vnY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a noun of number; (S, Msb;) applied to the dual number; (Msb;) meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Two;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"double of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAHidN","text_ar":"وَاحِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) with a conjunctive"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[when not immediately preceded by a quiescence, written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@vonaAni","text_ar":"ا@ثْنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (T, S, Msb;) but this is sometimes made disjunctive when connected with a preceding word by poetic license: (T, S:) of the masc. gender: (S:) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AivonataAni","text_ar":"اِثْنَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, Msb,) in which, also, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is conjunctive; (T, Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vinotaAni","text_ar":"ثِنْتَانِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T S, M, Msb, K;) the latter sometimes used, (T,) [much less frequently than the former, though the only fem. form mentioned in the M and K,] and of the dial. of Temeem; (Msb;) like as one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hiYa A@bonapu fulaAnK","text_ar":"هِىَ ا@بْنَةُ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hiYa binotuhu","text_ar":"هِىَ بِنْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T:) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the dual is a substitute for the final radical,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,) as it is in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asonatuwA","text_ar":"اَسْنَتُوا"},{"kind":"text","text":", the only other instance of this substitution except in words of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AifotaEala","text_ar":"اِفْتَعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Sb, M, TA:) in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AivonaAni","text_ar":"اِثْنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the final radical,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is suppressed: (Msb:) it has no sing.: (Lth, T:) if it were allowable to assign to it a sing., it would be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AivonN","text_ar":"اِثْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for the masc.] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AivonapN","text_ar":"اِثْنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for the fem.], like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonN","text_ar":"اِبْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonapN","text_ar":"اِبْنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) accord. to some, (Msb,) it is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vinoYN","text_ar":"ثِنْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, Msb, CK;) and hence the dual"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vinotaAni","text_ar":"ثِنْتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or it is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vanaYN","text_ar":"ثَنَىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb, and so in a copy of the K,) the conjunctive"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"being then substituted for the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"whence the dual"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@vonaAni","text_ar":"ا@ثْنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@bonaAni","text_ar":"ا@بْنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) this is shown by the form of its pl., which is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avonaA='N","text_ar":"اَثْنَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abonaA='N","text_ar":"اَبْنَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@bonN","text_ar":"ا@بْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaYN","text_ar":"بَنَىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banawN","text_ar":"بَنَوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=xaA='N","text_ar":"ا=خَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axN","text_ar":"اَخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axawN","text_ar":"اَخَوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) In the saying in the Kur [xvi. 53],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA tat~axi*uwA A_i`lhayoni","text_ar":"لَا تَتَّخِذُوا اـِٰلهَيْنِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@vonayoni","text_ar":"ا@ثْنَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Take not to yourselves two gods"},{"kind":"text","text":"], the last word is added as a corroborative. (M.) The phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vinotaA HanoZalK","text_ar":"ثِنْتَا حَنْظَلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs, by poetic license, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AivonataAni mino HanoZalK","text_ar":"اِثْنَتَانِ مِنْ حَنْظَلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HanoZalataAni","text_ar":"حَنْظَلَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Two colo-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":360},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cynths"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqadaHi","text_ar":"القَدَحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aribotu A^avonaA='a","text_ar":"شَرِبْتُ اَثْنَا=ءَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aribotu A@vonaYo h`*aA AlqadaHi","text_ar":"شَرِبْتُ ا@ثْنَىْ هٰذَا القَدَحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I drank"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"twice as much as the bowl,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as this bowl:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aribotu A@vonaYo mud~i AlbaSorapi","text_ar":"شَرِبْتُ ا@ثْنَىْ مُدِّ البَصْرَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@vonayoni","text_ar":"ا@ثْنَيْنِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bimud~i AlbaSorapi","text_ar":"بِمُدِّ البَصْرَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I drank twice the quantity of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mud~","text_ar":"مُدّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of El-Basrah"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) And a poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"↓ \n      famaA Hulibato A_il~aA Alv~alaAvapa waAlv~unaY\n                      \n                     \n                        walaA quy~ilato A_il~aA qariybFA maqaAluhaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And she was not milked save"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"three"},{"kind":"text","text":"vessels"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and two,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor was she given her middaydrink save when her midday-resting was near."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (IAar, M.) ―         -b2-  Hence, (Msb,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomu AlA@ivonayoni","text_ar":"يَوْمُ الا@ِثْنَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA@ivonaAni","text_ar":"الا@ِثْنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone, (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One of the days of the week;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the second;"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Monday;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] because the first, with the Arabs, is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aHadu","text_ar":"الاَحَدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~inaY","text_ar":"الثِّنَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY","text_ar":"اـِلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) so in the copies of the K; [or,] accord. to some, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~uniY~u","text_ar":"الثُّنِىُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~unuwYu","text_ar":"الثُّنُوىُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEuwl","text_ar":"فُعُول"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vudiY~N","text_ar":"ثُدِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vadoYN","text_ar":"ثَدْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], is used in this sense; (TA;) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alyawomu Alv~unaY~u","text_ar":"اليَوْمُ الثُّنَىُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [so in the M, accord. to the TT,] mentioned by Sb, on the authority of certain of the Arabs: (M:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avonaA='N","text_ar":"اَثْنَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avaAniynu","text_ar":"اَثَانِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) the latter mentioned on the authority of Th: but it has no dual: and those who say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avonaA='N","text_ar":"اَثْنَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"form this pl. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA@ivonu","text_ar":"الا@ِثْنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", although this has not been in use: (M:) or it has neither dual nor pl., (S, Msb,) being itself a dual; (S;) but if you would form a pl. from it, you would regard it as itself a sing., and make its pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avaAniynu","text_ar":"اَثَانِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb:) IB says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avaAniynu","text_ar":"اَثَانِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has not been heard [from the Arabs], and is only mentioned by Fr, on the ground of analogy; that it is far-fetched in respect of analogy; and that the pl. heard is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avonaA='N","text_ar":"اَثْنَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": Seer and others mention, as heard from the Arabs,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu layaSuwmu AlA^avonaA='a","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَيَصُومُ الاَثْنَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he fasts on the Mondays"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alvnyn","text_ar":"الثنين"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ywm Alvnyn","text_ar":"يوم الثنين"},{"kind":"text","text":"has no dim. (Sb, S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ams","text_ar":"امس"},{"kind":"text","text":".) IJ says that the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alvnyn","text_ar":"الثنين"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not redundant, though the word is not an epithet: Abu-l-'Abbás says that the prefixing of the article in this case is allowable because the virtual meaning is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alyawomu Alv~aAniY","text_ar":"اليَوْمُ الثَّانِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the second day"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) The saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alyawomu AlA@ivonaAni","text_ar":"اليَوْمُ الا@ِثْنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means The name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to-day"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAvnAn","text_ar":"الاثنان"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and is like the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alyawomu yawomaAni","text_ar":"اليَوْمُ يَوْمَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[to-day is two days] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alyawomu xamosapa Ea$ara mina Al$~ahori","text_ar":"اليَوْمُ خَمْسَةَ عَشَرَ مِنَ الشَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[to-day is fifteen of the month]. (Sb, M.) Sometimes,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomu A@vonayoni","text_ar":"يَوْمُ ا@ثْنَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", without the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurs in poetry. (M, K.) When a pronoun refers to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAvnAn","text_ar":"الاثنان"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as meaning Monday], this word may be treated in two ways, [as a sing. and as a dual,] but the more chaste way is to treat it as a sing., as meaning the day: (Msb:) [thus,] Aboo-Ziyád used to say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maDaY AlA@ivonaAni bimaA fiyhi","text_ar":"مَضَى الا@ِثْنَانِ بِمَا فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Monday passed with what"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurred"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; making it sing. and masc.; and thus he did in the case of every day of the week, except that he made"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljumoEap","text_ar":"الجُمْعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"fem.: Abu-I-Jarráh used to say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maDaY AlA@ivonaAni bimaA fiyhimaA","text_ar":"مَضَى الا@ِثْنَانِ بِمَا فِيهِمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", treating the word as a numeral; and thus he treated the third and fourth and fifth days, saying in each of these cases"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bimaA fiyhin~a","text_ar":"بِمَا فِيهِنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) ―         -b3-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AivonaA Ea$ara","text_ar":"اِثْنَا عَشَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AivonataA Ea$orapa","text_ar":"اِثْنَتَا عَشْرَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; respectively, in a case of nasb and khafd,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AivonaYo Ea$ara","text_ar":"اِثْنَىْ عَشَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AivonataYo Ea$orapa","text_ar":"اِثْنَتَىْ عَشْرَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@","text_ar":"ا@"},{"kind":"text","text":"when not immediately preceded by a quiescence; mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Twelve:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$arapN","text_ar":"عَشَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["T","S","Msb","M","TA","Sb","Lth","K"]}]}}